claim.claim-text:
84. A tire inflation assistance system comprising: 
a tire pressure sensor adapted for sensing pressure of a tire mounted on a wheel of a vehicle, the tire being pressurized by a gas; 
a valve stem adapted for allowing the gas to be introduced into or escape from the tire; 
a controller for receiving input from said tire pressure sensor; and 
a vibrator element, said controller producing an output to cause said vibrator element to vibrate as a function of the pressurized gas in the tire to thereby provide a tactile indication of the tire pressure condition of the vehicle tire at said valve stem.
